# batch-pr-ci-fix-workflow — Version History

## v2.10.0 (2026-04-27)

**Changed by:** HomericIntelligence ecosystem — fleet-wide gitleaks-action@v2 replacement across 11 repos (chore/merge-typecheck-into-lint wave)
**Verification:** verified-ci

### What changed
- Added Phase 8.1: Fix gitleaks-action@v2 in ALL workflow files per repo (not just _required.yml)
- Added Phase 8.2: Fix yamllint failing on long lines (use -d relaxed)
- Added Phase 8.3: Fix mypy traversing pytest internals (--no-namespace-packages --python-version 3.11)
- Added Phase 8.4: Fix multi-line python3 -c breaking YAML parsing at column 1
- Added Phase 8.5: Verify CI after force-push via workflow run head_sha (not mergeStateStatus)
- Added Swarm Agent Prompt Template Hygiene section
- Added 8 new Failed Attempts rows covering the above patterns
- Added 5 new When to Use triggers (items 24–28)
- Updated description to include triggers (24)–(28)
- Updated date to 2026-04-27
- Bumped version from 2.9.0 to 2.10.0

### Why
Fleet-wide gitleaks-action@v2 → curl binary install across 11 HomericIntelligence repos
(chore/merge-typecheck-into-lint wave, 2026-04-26) uncovered 5 additional CI failure patterns:

1. **Legacy ci.yml** (ProjectTelemachy): `_required.yml` was fixed but `ci.yml` still had the
   action. Must grep ALL workflow files per repo, not just `_required.yml`.
2. **yamllint line-length** (ProjectMnemosyne): default config treats lines >80 chars as errors;
   URL-heavy workflow files fail immediately. Fix: `yamllint -d relaxed`.
3. **mypy pytest internals** (ProjectMnemosyne): `mypy scripts/ tests/` traversed into pytest,
   hitting Python 3.10 pattern matching. Fix: `--no-namespace-packages --python-version 3.11`.
4. **YAML column-1 python3 -c** (ProjectAgamemnon): Multi-line Python in `run: |` with lines
   at column 1 broke YAML parsing. Fix: collapse to single line.
5. **mergeStateStatus lag** (general): After force-push, `mergeStateStatus` shows BLOCKED even
   when new CI run passed. Fix: verify via `gh api .../actions/runs?branch=...` head_sha.

Additionally documented swarm prompt template hygiene after a `tr '[:lower']'` typo (missing `:`)
in the orchestrator prompt was copied verbatim by Haiku into ProjectHermes workflow files.

