## v2.9.0 (2026-04-24)

**Changed by:** HomericIntelligence/Myrmidons CI fix session — apply.yml pixi migration, bats PATH isolation, companion script guard (PR #307)
**Verification:** verified-ci

### What changed
- Added Phase 20: Fix GHA workflow using manual pixi install instead of composite setup-pixi action
- Added Phase 21: Fix bats PATH isolation for pixi-managed tools (use /usr/sbin:/sbin not /bin:/usr/bin)
- Added Phase 22: Guard companion script calls for unit test temp-dir isolation
- Added 3 new Failed Attempts rows covering the above patterns
- Added 3 new When to Use triggers (items 21–23)
- Updated description to include triggers (21)–(23)
- Updated date to 2026-04-24

### Why
Myrmidons CI fix session (2026-04-24) uncovered three independent CI failure patterns:
1. apply.yml was written before the .github/actions/setup-pixi composite action existed and
   used manual pixi install that failed because pixi itself was never installed on the runner.
2. bats tests for "tool missing" used PATH="/usr/bin:/bin" which pixi activation had already
   extended with conda-forge paths — the tool was findable, making the assertion fail.
3. validate-schemas.sh was updated to call validate-fleet-refs.sh at the end, but unit tests
   copy only the main script to a temp dir — the companion exec failed, breaking 3 tests.

