## v2.8.0 (2026-04-23)

**Changed by:** HomericIntelligence ecosystem CI fix — just v1.14+ keyword conflict, gitleaks asset URL fix
**Verification:** verified-ci

### What changed
- Added just v1.14+ `import` keyword reservation pattern — inline Python heredocs in justfile recipes break `just --list`, causing all Code Quality CI to fail
- Added gitleaks-action@v2 unauthorized exit — HomericIntelligence org requires curl-based install with correct asset URL (lowercase OS, x64 arch mapping)
- Updated description triggers (19) and (20)
- Bumped version from 2.7.0 to 2.8.0

### Why
just v1.14+ treats `import` as a reserved keyword for justfile module imports. Any inline
`python3 -c "\ import json..."` in a justfile recipe causes `just --list` to fail with
"Unknown start of token ';'", breaking all Code Quality CI jobs that call `just --list`.
gitleaks-action@v2 requires a paid GitHub org license — HomericIntelligence free-tier org
accounts see "unauthorized" exit 1; the fix uses curl-based gitleaks install with the
correct asset URL (uname -s → lowercase; uname -m x86_64 → x64).

